all of this is just my opinion, but all you have to do is look at things for what they are or aren't, and then not let the internet insist everything you see is easily explained- by things like optical illusions, rem, etc.

content.summary: Huge string of light found on pictures of night sky after the fact, moved west during 10-15 second interval between pictures.

content.detailedDescription: Was in armada, mi at the time, about 7:30pm est.  just finished mowing the grass as it was getting dark, but still dusk.  was talking with friend outside his house and turned to south.  freaked out and saw a bright half-moon shaped bright light coming from rear of flight object hovering in air.  vehicle was hovering until the light appeared, then took off in a straight path to the east and disappeared almost immediately.  not sure the speed, but it was a fast event.  just caught the light and saw the object (dark grey/charcoal surface).  rounded and curved on top and bottom..Appeared symmetrical.  top and bottom were almost like a thinner, aerodynamic shape.  smooth and curved on top and bottom.  freaked out and told buddy i was talking to, he said he just caught the light and didn't see whole thing.  feelings = freaked out, amazed, awestruck, curious.  lost sight as it immediately (and quickly) took off after bright light appeared from rear.  this was no blimp, plane, military aircraft, drone, experimental aircraft nothing.  it seemed to rise out of nowhere because i just saw turned around and saw it hovering about a couple miles away, then it took off.  amazing, will never forget it.
content.summary: Finished mowing lawn just before dark, turned to south, saw half-moon bright light from rear, then it took off in a straight path eastward.

content.summary: Over sized , dark object with lot of different colored bright lights , silent traveling above my building se

content.detailedDescription: I walked out of my side door to go to my truck. the sky was dark as the moon was less than half.I first noticed it in the south west sky and thought it was a jet. it was very large (bigger than venus or jupiter look like) and moving steadily at a moderate speed. my wife came out with binoculars so i could look for aircraft lights, like the blinking green or red lights common to jets. none. just a bright object on a steady path. after following it as it moved towards the northeast it got dim and faded out. the trajectory was steady and took about 2 or 3 minutes to go over the sky...A lot faster than a 5 mile high jet would have done the same path. i believe i saw my first ufo. it certainly was not a jet or airplane.
content.summary: It appeared brighter and much larger than what jupiter or venus look like

content.detailedDescription: Object seen was a solid, black equilateral with 4 arms on each side. the arms were made up of connected circles that all met at a larger circle in the very center. i can compare the color of the black closest to being matte, it had no sheen. it was just dense blackness that i wouldn't even consider truly matte but it's the closest comparison i can make. i was outside on my friend's balcony with 2 of our other friends. the three others went inside and i chose to stay outside for a minute, no particular reason why. i stand and face towards the sandia mountains where i see tthis object. it comes completely out of nowhere and i'm entranced by it. it moves towards me with its arms moving in a fluid up-and-down motion and in sync. at the point it was so close that in seconds it could've been in arm's reach, i, without thought, slowly turn my head towards my house to the left (directly across the street) of me, stare, turn back, and the object is gone. the only possible explanation would be a hallucination, although i know i was fine. i did not personally  choose to look directly at my house . i was not scared at all and experienced zero fear during or after. i would consider it  a long interaction for it having been so personal. if it were reported and people had seen it there would be a crisis and i don't know why i was the only one who saw it.
content.summary: Ufo approaches me from direction of mountains

content.detailedDescription:
1) i was outside going for a run. i was running west and looking out into the horizon at the sky. it was night-time.

2) i was looking at the sky, and in the center of my field of vision, a bright light appeared out of nowhere, zipped upward super quickly, then disappeared. i've seen shooting stars and this was not a shooting star.

3) i really didn't know what it was. i knew immediately it wasn't anything i've seen before.

4) as mentioned above, i just saw a bright light, brighter than a star, appear suddenly, out of nowhere, as if it powered on, then it zipped upward super fast then disappeared.

5) as soon as i saw this happen, i knew immediately this was not an airplane, satellite, or shooting star. i knew i witnessed something else entirely.

6) as it zipped upward it simply disappeared on it's own- it faded away as quickly as it appeared.
content.summary: Bright light appeared, zipped upward super fast, then disappeared

content.detailedDescription: I got up to use the bathroom at about 1 am in my house. when i was going to the bathroom, i heard what sounded like a loud humming coming from outside of the house. it sounded like it was coming from right above the house. this sound lasted for about five minutes, then it faded away. i didn't bother to look, because the noise really creeped me out. i was just happy that it stopped! we've heard some creepy noises around here, but this one was really terrifying. the first odd noise we heard was a few years ago during a meteor shower my daughter woke us up at about 2 or 3 am in the fall to see. we were out there for awhile when we heard a loud screaming coming from the north west. scared the hell out of us. my daughter wanted to go have a look, but i made the two of us go back inside. this humming, though, was the longest bizarre noise we've heard around here.
content.summary: Loud humming-sound that was not drone-like

content.detailedDescription:
Soy pescador y pesco en el mar casi siempre, este año con todos en la familia compramos una oroch y estábamos de viaje para ver si la pesca de los lagos de la cordillera nos puede dar mejor ganancia porque acá las cosas económicas están muy mal.
estuvimos dos semanas recorriendo los lagos san martín, cardiel, strobel y quiroga hablando con la gente de ahí y seguíamos viaje para el norte al pueyrredón, ghio y lago buenos aires, vamos lento porque los caminos están bastante malos.
paramos en la curva de las horquetas para almorzar y estirarnos antes de entrar en la pampa del asador sobre la ruta nacional 40, mientras estábamos en esto se apareció un objeto ovalado, para decir se parecía a un chancho sin cabeza patas para arriba muy grande como de 8 a 10 metros.
era de color plateado brillante y volaba bajo y paso por arriba de nosotros y después empezó como a bailar en el aire y subía, bajaba y daba giros y estuvo así por un cuarto de hora.
había aparecido desde el lado de la cordillera y se fue para el norte, al rato seguimos viaje y antes de terminar la recta como a 40 km de donde estábamos nos paró un estanciero de la zona que iba con su señora y su hijo y una traffic que era de ellos y tenía el chofer y un guía y además 14 turistas chinos.
nos preguntaron si habíamos visto algo raro sobre la ruta y les contamos lo del objeto volador y nos dijeron que todos ellos habían visto lo mismo y que algunos le habían sacado fotos y videos.
le dejamos nuestro mail para que si podían nos manden alguna foto porque nosotros no sacamos ninguna y el estanciero nos dijo que lo iba a hacer.
por lo que nos contaron era lo mismo y la señora dijo que era como un colador de fideos redondo de los viejos con patitas dado vuelta.
el estanciero nos contó que un puestero de su estancia había visto hacía como una semana atrás un par de helicópteros blancos dando vueltas por la zona del paso roballos bien adentro de la cordillera y que uno de ellos aterrizó al oeste del monte zeballos mientras el oro daba vueltas por la zona en grandes círculos como buscando algo.
mas adelante ese mismo día después de cruzar el río pinturas en la meseta de bajo caracoles vimos parados al costado de la ruta cinco 4x4 importados y un camión como los del camel tropy con una parabólica y antenas arriba, todos de color blanco y tenían en sus puertas un símbolo como un círculo atravesado de arriba a abajo por una línea y algunas letras y números.
nos íbamos a parar pero alguien vestido con un traje blanco, había varios así vestidos, como los que usaron en el edificio de nisman nos hizo señas para que siguiéramos.
mucho mas adelante y unos 10 km antes de llegar a perito moreno, en plena peladero nos paró un reten policial y nos preguntaron de donde veníamos y si habíamos tenido alguna novedad en el viaje, nos asustamos un poco por el lugar donde nos pararon y no les dijimos nada.
esa noche tomando unos tragos en el bar de perito moreno y hablando con la gente parece que otras personas vieron lo que nosotros y que era un comentario en el pueblo, pero como que todos hablaban por lo bajo.
content.summary: Ovni por la pampa del asador en santa cruz argentina
